## Architecture Considerations (Long-term)

### SwiftData Migration
- Current: Uses Core Data with NSPersistentCloudKitContainer
- Future: Could migrate to SwiftData for more modern persistence
- Blocker: Need to ensure CloudKit compatibility

### Observable Macro
- Current: Uses ObservableObject + @Published (requires Combine import)
- Future: Could migrate to @Observable macro (iOS 17+)
- Benefit: Remove Combine dependency, simpler code, better performance

### Structured Concurrency
- Current: Mix of Task.detached and Task { @MainActor }
- Future: Could use actors more consistently
- Benefit: Better thread safety guarantees

### Protocol-Based ViewModel Testing
- Current: ViewModels directly reference CoreDataManager.shared
- Future: Inject dependencies via protocols for mock testing
- Benefit: Unit tests for ViewModel logic without Core Data stack
